# 3D Chart - KX Dashboards

Original URL: https://code.kx.com/dashboards/3dchart/

# 3D Chart

![Screenshot](../img/3dcharts/3dchartshtmllight.jpg)

Charts data in three dimensions

## Set up

  1. Set up a data source, available in Layers.

  2. For each x-, y-, and z-axis, define data columns to plot with _Data Description_.

  3. Add _Labels_ for each axis

## Basics

![Screenshot](../img/3dcharts/3dchartsbasicsmenu.png)

_Name_

    A name for the component provided by the user. 
_Focus_

    Used for [linking components](../viewstateparameters/#linking-components). Requires a [View State Parameter](../viewstateparameters/).
_Selected Value_ and _Selected Value Attribute_

     [Selected values](../viewstateparameters/#selected-values)

## Layers

Ability to display multiple different data sources on the same chart.
![Screenshot](../img/3dcharts/3dchartslayer.png)

_Type_ ![Screenshot](../img/3dcharts/3dcharttypehtmllight.jpg)

_Data Source_

    A [query or analytic](../datasources/)
_Name_

    Assign a name for each layer.
_X-Axis_

_Y-Axis_

_Z-Axis_

_Volume_

    Select data columns to plot from the data source.

## Axis controls

![Screenshot](../img/3dcharts/3dchartsxmenu.jpg)

Settings for (each of) the X-, Y- and Z-axes

_Axis Type_

    Axis scaling; select from `linear` or `category`
_Label_

    Descriptive label for the axis
_Format_

    Numeric or date format; select from `General`, `Number`, `Smart Number`, `Formatted Number` or `Datetime`
_Set Min Axis Value_

_AxisMin_

_Set Max Axis Value_

_AxisMax_

    Manually define min and max rage of axis
_Decimal Places_

    Where a numeric value is used in _Format_ , define the number of decimal places to display
_Date/Time Format_

    For `Datetime`, define the Date/Time format to use
_Prefix_

    Character before axis label
_Suffix_

    Character after axis label

## Volume

![Screenshot](../img/3dcharts/3dvolume.jpg)

_Set Min Axis Value_

_AxisMin_

_Set Max Axis Value_

_AxisMax_

    Manually define min and max rage of axis

## Position

Orientation of the chart: use the sliders or select Preview mode and rotate
the chart, using the mouse scroll wheel to zoom in and out.

![Screenshot](../img/3dcharts/positionmenu.jpg)

## Style

![Screenshot](../img/3dcharts/3dchartstyle.jpg)

_Stroke_

    Define grid-line color
_Fill_

    Define background color for component
_Advanced CSS_

     [Advanced CSS](../style/#advanced-css)
_Custom tooltip_

     [Custom tooltip](../template/#custom-tooltips)
_Vertical Ratio_

    Extends the height of the chart
_Keep Aspect Ratio_

    Maintain aspect ratio when interacting with the chart
_CSS Classes_

    Can be applied to style the component

[Style](../style/#component-style) for common style settings

